{"name":"Legendary","flags":{"forgeoflegends":{"path":"skills/legendary"}},"pages":[{"name":"Legendary","type":"text","title":{"show":false,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h3 id=\"legendary\">Legendary</h3>\n\n<p>A legendary skill is unique to a legendary foe or a character’s personal legend.</p>"},"_id":"jBuozZlPLSG36nrH","image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"cZY121Eik0C03v39":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"forgeoflegends","systemVersion":"0.4","coreVersion":"10.290","createdTime":1668273498396,"modifiedTime":1668273498396,"lastModifiedBy":"cZY121Eik0C03v39"},"_id":"z7qN766r4PQsEaMg"}
{"name":"Fate","flags":{"forgeoflegends":{"path":"playing/fate"}},"pages":[{"name":"Fate","type":"text","title":{"show":false,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<div title=\"Fate\">\n\t<h1 id=\"fate--doom\">Fate &amp; Doom</h1>\n\n<p>Fate is funny thing. Heroes, especially those who stay true to themselves and to their friends, often find that destiny is on their side. In Forge of Legends, fate is a system for rewarding players for expressing their characters’ personality, and for giving players some control over the game world beyond the actions of their characters.\nPlayers will gain fate through fateful deeds: momentous decisions which are described in the <a class=\"keyword\" title=\"personality\" data-path=\"personality\">Personality</a> section. Characters also gain fate whenever one of their background details poses a significant obstacle to themselves or the group, as determined by the GM. Some GMs may choose to award fate points to players who make the game more fun for everyone, such as taking an amazing risk or spouting an exceptional joke.\nWhen a player earns a fate point, they should add it to their total number and keep track of them. Each player may save up to 3 fate points at a time. If a player already has 3 fate points when they earn another, they may give their new fate point to another player instead.  Note that fate points belong to an individual player, not merely their character. Players may gain and spend fate points even in situations where their character is not present, if the GM deems it appropriate.</p>\n<h2 id=\"twists-of-fate\">Twists of Fate</h2>\n\n<p>Players may spend their fate points by invoking a twist of fate at any time to add detail to the game world. Some common twists of fate would be: adding a feature to the environment, adding an item to their character’s inventory, or embellishing their character’s background, all of which may add bonuses or penalties. Any detail, no matter the subject and no matter how large or small, can be invoked by a twist of fate. However, players may only add detail, not remove or change details that have already been established.\nWhen a player declares that they would like to invoke a twist of fate, they should describe the detail they would like to add to the world. The game master then decides if that detail could reasonably exist, and if it hasn’t already been established. If so, the player may spend their fate point and the detail they suggested is added to the game world. Alternatively, a successful <a class=\"keyword\" title=\"challenge\" data-path=\"playing/challenge\">challenge</a> might allow a player to invoke a twist of fate for free!</p>\n\n<h2 id=\"doom\">Doom</h2>\n\n<p>The doom pool represents long term complications that impose obstacles between them and their goals. Many things can generate doom, such as failing challenges, dawdling in dangerous locales, and the machinations of the villains. The GM Guidelines section dictates how the GM can use doom, but it will always be used to cause problems for the players. Players should try their best to minimize the amount of doom the GM accrues.</p>\n \n</div>"},"_id":"LaoOPi3VeTAOzJib","image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"cZY121Eik0C03v39":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"forgeoflegends","systemVersion":"0.4","coreVersion":"10.290","createdTime":1668273484020,"modifiedTime":1668273484020,"lastModifiedBy":"cZY121Eik0C03v39"},"_id":"zSaw5tZQI4IMul4F"}
{"name":"Turns & Rounds","flags":{"forgeoflegends":{"path":"combat/turns-rounds"}},"pages":[{"name":"Turns & Rounds","type":"text","title":{"show":false,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2 id=\"turns--rounds\">Turns &amp; Rounds</h2>\n\n<p>Combat begins as soon as one character does something that other characters witness and are willing and able to oppose. That first acting character takes the first turn of combat. Any other characters may use a <a class=\"keyword\" title=\"reaction\" data-path=\"skills/reaction\">reaction</a> to immediately draw any <a class=\"keyword\" title=\"weapon\" data-path=\"skills/weapon\">weapons</a> they have equipped.\nA character may use two <a class=\"keyword\" title=\"a&gt; on their turn, one &lt;a class=\" data-path=\"skill\">skills</a> on their turn, one <a href=\"skills/action\">action</a> and one <a class=\"keyword\" title=\"maneuver\" data-path=\"skills/maneuver\">maneuver</a>. Actions typically involve <a class=\"keyword\" title=\"attacking\" data-path=\"combat/attacking\">attacking</a> enemies or supporting allies, while maneuvers typically involve moving to a better location or preparing for another skill. A character may use reactions on their own turn, as well as during other characters’ turns. Characters must typically finish one action before starting another; a character can’t move a few spaces with a maneuver, use an action, then finish the rest of the maneuver’s movement.\nOnce a character has finished their turn, an enemy character takes a turn. Typically, combat will occur between the group player characters and one group of NPCs controlled by the GM. When an enemy NPC finishes a turn, the players will collaborate to choose one of their characters who has not yet acted to take the next turn. When a player character finishes their turn, the GM will choose one NPC combatant who has not taken a turn to take the next turn. This cycle continues until all characters have taken their turns.\nIf all characters on one side have taken their turns, and other characters on the enemy side have not, then the other side may take their turns back to back until all characters have taken a turn. Once the last character in the combat has taken their turn, the round ends. Whichever side took the last turn of the previous round must let the opposing side act first on the next round. Some effects, especially environmental effects, do something at the end of the round. Once all characters have taken their turns, these effects should be resolved before the next round begins.</p>\n\n<blockquote>\n\n  <h3 id=\"advanced-turn-rules\">Advanced Turn Rules</h3>\n\n  <p>The above rules cover the majority of combat situations, but these rules clarify how turns work in more unusual circumstances. If one side of the combatants includes both players and NPCs, the players should decide when the NPCs on their side take their turns as if they were also player characters. If a combat includes three or more groups with mutually competing goals, the GM may decide to form three or more sides taking turns in order. Some powerful creatures, especially legendary foes, may take multiple turns in a single round. If they fight alongside lesser minions, then they may choose to take their turns back to back after the players’ near the start of the round, or let their minions act first and use their multiple turns in succession toward then end of the round.</p>\n</blockquote>"},"_id":"pa2i8aei0bbx4Bsp","image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"cZY121Eik0C03v39":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"forgeoflegends","systemVersion":"0.4","coreVersion":"10.290","createdTime":1668273484640,"modifiedTime":1668273484640,"lastModifiedBy":"cZY121Eik0C03v39"},"_id":"zTf98udGJqsiVvxC"}
{"name":"Obscuring Cloud","flags":{"forgeoflegends":{"path":"special-terrain/obscuring-cloud"}},"pages":[{"name":"Obscuring Cloud","type":"text","title":{"show":false,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h3 id=\"obscuring-cloud\">Obscuring Cloud</h3>\n\n<p>An obscuring cloud fills the are above the terrain with dense mist or smoke. Characters are unable to see more than one space through an obscuring cloud. Abilities that pass through more than one space of obscuring terrain can’t be aimed properly and are ineffective, unless they are area abilities (but not line abilities). All visual actions suffer a bane against targets in an obscuring cloud, and characters in an obscuring cloud have their perception decreased by two.\nThe obscuring cloud dissipates at the end of the round if it can flow downhill or if a strong wind is present, otherwise it lasts 1 minute. Depending on the source, an obscuring cloud may also exist underwater, at the GM’s discretion.</p>"},"_id":"r2B6ElnkQoRAa14n","image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"cZY121Eik0C03v39":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"forgeoflegends","systemVersion":"0.4","coreVersion":"10.290","createdTime":1668273498574,"modifiedTime":1668273498574,"lastModifiedBy":"cZY121Eik0C03v39"},"_id":"zbg15TjvWX7drs0D"}
{"name":"Slow","flags":{"forgeoflegends":{"path":"skills/slow"}},"pages":[{"name":"Slow","type":"text","title":{"show":false,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h3 id=\"slow\">Slow</h3><p>A slow <a class=\"keyword\" title=\"maneuver\" data-path=\"skills/maneuver\">maneuver</a> doesn’t let a character move their <a class=\"keyword\" title=\"bonus-speed\" data-path=\"abilities/bonus-speed\">bonus speed</a> as part of the skill. Slow maneuvers may still let the character move a specific number of spaces.</p>","markdown":""},"_id":"io4IFXRkxv7KntQM","image":{},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"cZY121Eik0C03v39":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"forgeoflegends","systemVersion":"0.4","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1668273498440,"modifiedTime":1674660452980,"lastModifiedBy":"cZY121Eik0C03v39"},"_id":"ACOGH0LeT3OOycAc"}
